cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a model for dependency parsing and language generation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the model is parameterized by Hierarchical Pitman-Yor Processes and performs semi-supervised learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an efficient decoding algorithm based on particle filtering. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is an unlikely category as the paper does not relate to sound or audio processing.
